d=maximumstorage>MaximumStorage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/15/03 12:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=593.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My results from back then</span><hr size=1> Done on pendragon with old epic armor. I posted this before but I can't find it so here it is again. I decided not to add the text logs of each fight and just the calculations done after parsing them.<br>
<br>
Level 50 Warrior: 54hammer, 1204weap skill and it's a 97 quality 2h arc hammer.<br>
<br>
Target is a level 50 skald 15% crush resist total<br>
<br>
Testing RA's Avoid Pain2-3 and Armor of Faith2 (AP and AF)<br>
<br>
Note: When using Avoid Pain and you click your bonus button your actual melee resist<br>
% does not increase there. Delving the buff shows function: melee absorb, Value: 10 <br>
or 20 or 30 depending on the level of AP.<br>
<br>
Note: When using Armor of Faith which is supposed to be +50 AF per level your AF on<br>
your character sheet displays much higher. Mine displayed 762 which turns out is<br>
(635 +50*AFLevel * (1+absfactor)) = 635 + 100 * 1.27 = 762 while using AF2 which <br>
means that this spells armor boost is based on your armor types absorb factor and <br>
would give you less armor boost if you were wearing studded or lower and more if you<br>
had on plate.<br>
<br>
Note: The averages below may vary somewhat during testing because I didn't do<br>
enough trials to represent a good solid average of weapon damages. Waiting 15 minutes <br>
on the RA timers to reset for 60 seconds worth of taking damage requires a healer<br>
to continually heal you and the time it would take to get a good statistical sample<br>
would be so long no one wants to do it. But overall if enough tests are done I think <br>
it will reflect similar findings with %dmg reductions deviating less from the advertised<br>
RA absorb amount.<br>
<br>
DMG W/O RAs<br>
------------------<br>
AVG BASE DMG + AVG STYLE DMG = AVG TOTAL DMG<br>
<br>
177.1 (-31.2) + 69.3 style = 246.4 avg dmg. AP2 test.<br>
<br>
210.3 (-37.1) + 79.1 style = 289.4 avg dmg. AF2 test.<br>
<br>
155.2 (-27.3) + 63.3 style = 218.5 avg dmg. AF2 + AP2 test.<br>
<br>
156.2 (-27.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  + 63.1 style = 219.3 avg dmg. AP3 / AP3 + AF2 test.<br>
<br>
Avg across all tests: 174.7 (-30.85) + 68.7 style avg = 243.4<br>
<br>
DMG WITH RAs<br>
------------------<br>
AVG BASE DMG + AVG STYLE DMG = AVG TOTAL DMG<br>
<br>
123.7 (-22.0) + 50.2 style avg = 173.9 AP2 test<br>
<br>
140.1 (-24.6) + 56.1 style avg = 196.2 AF2 test<br>
<br>
110.9 (-19.6) + 42.5 style avg = 153.4 AF2 + AP2 Test<br>
<br>
117.2 (-20.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  + 44.7 style avg = 161.9 AP3 test<br>
<br>
100.5 (-17.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  + 38.0 style avg = 138.5 AP3 + AF2 test<br>
<br>
COMPARISON<br>
------------------<br>
AP2: (243.4 - 173.9) / 243.4 = 28.5 % dmg decrease<br>
<br>
AF2: (243.4 - 196.2) / 243.4 = 19.4% dmg decrease<br>
<br>
AP2 + AF2: (243.4 - 153.4)/ 243.4 = 37% dmg decrease<br>
<br>
AP3: (243.4 - 161.9) / 243.4 = 33.4% dmg decrease<br>
<br>
AP3 + AF2: (243.4 - 138.5) / 243.4 = 43.1 % dmg decrease<br>
<br>
<br>
SECOND RUN OF TESTS (PVE)- ICESTRIDER INTERCEPTOR WITH 26% thrust resist<br>
<br>
AVG 71.6 (-13.7) NO RA      <br>
AVG 44.4 (-8.3)  AP3&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp (71.6 - 44.4) / 71.6 = 38% dmg absorb<br>
AVG 62.4 (-11.9) AF2&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp (71.6 - 62.4) / 71.6 = 12.85% dmg absorb<br>
AVG 38.8 (-7.4)  AP3 + AF2&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp (71.6 - 38.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  / 71.6 = 45.8% dmg absorb<br>
<br>
CONCLUSION: When used at the same time its clear that the dmg absorbtion isnt stacked<br>
together and is most likely done in sequence lessening the dmg absorbed by that buff <br>
compared to when it is used alone however the total dmg absorbed is still greater <br>
than just using each buff alone.<br>
<br>
